  "prompt": "Why was the part B in 70 marks theory of physical education removed by CBSE for the batch 2014-2015 class 12th?",
  "response": "The Central Board of Secondary Education (CBSE) periodically reviews and updates its curriculum and assessment methods to align with educational goals, as well as to accommodate new teaching methodologies and changes in educational policy. For the batch of 2014-2015, CBSE made adjustments to the assessment pattern in physical education, which included removing part B from the 70 marks theory component.\n\nThe specific reasons for these changes can include:\n\n1. **Curriculum Update:** CBSE often revises its curriculum, and changes in the theory component could be part of a broader effort to streamline content, make it more relevant to current educational demands, or to ensure a more balanced distribution of marks between theory and practical components.\n\n2. **Focus on Practical Skills:** Physical education as a subject places significant importance on practical skill development. Reducing the weight of theoretical components might be aimed at increasing the emphasis on practical assessments where students demonstrate physical capabilities, skills, and fitness levels.\n\n3. **Feedback from Educators and Stakeholders:** Changes like these are sometimes a result of feedback from teachers, students, and other stakeholders who might advocate for a more appropriate balance between theory and practice in physical education.\n\n4. **Educational Policy Changes:** Occasionally, shifts in national educational policy can influence how subjects are taught and assessed. CBSE revisions could be part of aligning with new guidelines, pedagogical approaches, or policy directives aimed at improving educational outcomes.\n\nFor the precise reason or official statement, it would be best to refer to the CBSE notifications from that period or communicate directly with CBSE for comprehensive information.",
